      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Compound <b>A</b>, C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>18</sub>O, undergoes reaction with dilute H<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub> at 50 °C to yield a mixture of two alkenes, C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>16</sub>. The major alkene product, <b>B</b>, gives only cyclopentanone after ozone treatment followed by reduction with zinc in acetic acid. Identify <b>A</b> and <b>B</b>, and write the reactions.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcUlTIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--c7029f2f9fb1eb19cf6d3ccf17ee98fb8163f624/OChem_08_EC_046.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of cyclopentanone.\">",
